Former Nigerian youth international, Félix Orode, is set to join a top Paraguayan club.  The experienced attacking midfielder who played for the Flying Eagles during the Qualifiers for the U-20 World Cup in Canada and San Lorenzo de Almagro (Argentine First Division), a team in which he was coached by Diego Cholo Simeone, is close to signing with a Paraguayan First League Club according to the player’s O Argentine representative, Juan Saravi Platero who is in Asunción, Paraguay to seal the deal. “I had talks with Guaraní but unfortunately I did not pass the phase in the Copa Libertadores, a continental tournament equivalent to the Champion League and there is no possibility of signing up for the local tournament because the window for passes is closed, ” Saravi said. “There is still a possibility with General Caballero, Sol de America or Nacional who play Copa Sudamericana, a tournament equivalent to the Europa League.   IWD: SWAN wants more women in sports management     Scotland, Ukraine WC playoff postponed     Success still yearns for Eagles call up   ” Another alternative would be the option of playing Intermediate (Paraguay second division) with Sportivo Luqueño, a traditional Premier League team.” Orode is expected to sign a one-year deal with a clause allowing him to be transferred to Europe or South Africa in June. “It is important that Felix Orode plays a continental tournament now and that he can be known and considered by the Super Eagles coach, having played U20 and his extensive career can bring a new style and pace of play to Nigeria, ” Saravi added.